      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Competitive. LANTANA (1) was a tough winner in this grade last start to continue a strong run of form, racing on speed and running out a half-length winner. She sets up very nicely from the soft gate and will take plenty of catching again. CIRCUS LIGHTS (4) was a narrow maiden winner at Ballarat Synthetic at her second career start. She can continue to improve and gets the handy 3kg claim for Jabez Johnstone. TAN TAT DELIGHT (6) struggled last time on heavy going at Sandown Lakeside but had been close up prior in a good race and can bounce back. Wary of debut winner JENNI AGOGO (3) who looked good at Pakenham Synthetic as a $13 chance. Onto turf here but warrants respect. HI VAL (5) was behind LANTANA last time but is in the mix.",
